---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import FeatureSection from '../components/FeatureSection.astro';
import Card from '../components/Card.astro';
import CardGrid from '../components/CardGrid.astro';
---
<Layout>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>From a Clinical Problem to a Human-Centered Mission</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">
        A story about how a startup feature evolved into a PhD project aimed at creating a shared language for our emotional lives.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <FeatureSection
    title="The Spark: From Startup to Science"
    theme="dark"
    imagePosition="left"
    videoSrc="https://videos.pexels.com/video-files/4787235/4787235-hd_1920_1080_25fps.mp4"
  >
    <p>
      This is where the story of your previous startup 'IntelliHearts' will go. You can describe the side feature that led to the realization about the huge demand for affective computing in health.
    </p>
  </FeatureSection>

  <FeatureSection
    title="Early Validation & Academic Rigor"
    theme="light"
    imagePosition="right"
    imageSrc="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1454165804606-c3d57bc86b40?q=80&w=2070"
    imageAlt="A person analyzing graphs and data on a screen"
    linkUrl="#"
  >
    <p>
      Here, you can tell the story of publishing your first paper on the topic with Vincenzo. This demonstrates early expertise and validation of your ideas. The image will link to your publication.
    </p>
  </FeatureSection>

  <FeatureSection
    title="The Path to a PhD"
    theme="dark"
    imagePosition="left"
    imageSrc="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1523050854058-8df90110c9f1?q=80&w=2070"
    imageAlt="University campus with graduates"
  >
    <p>
      This section will detail your journey to the scholarship at UWE, working with David during your MSc, and Michael's suggestion to pursue a PhD. It's the personal link between your past work and current research.
    </p>
  </FeatureSection>

  <section class="team-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>My Supervisors & Advisors</h2>
      <p class="subtitle">The team providing invaluable guidance for this project.</p>
      <CardGrid>
        <Card name="David" title="Director of Studies" imgSrc="https://placekitten.com/400/400" imgAlt="Photo of David" />
        <Card name="Michael" title="Second Supervisor" imgSrc="https://placekitten.com/401/401" imgAlt="Photo of Michael" />
        <Card name="Miles" title="Third Supervisor" imgSrc="https://placekitten.com/402/402" imgAlt="Photo of Miles" />
        <Card name="Paul" title="Fourth Supervisor" imgSrc="https://placekitten.com/403/403" imgAlt="Photo of Paul" />
      </CardGrid>
    </div>
  </section>

  <FeatureSection
    title="Our Human-Centered Approach"
    theme="light"
    imagePosition="right"
    imageSrc="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1557426272-fc759fdf7a8d?q=80&w=2070"
    imageAlt="A diverse team collaborating around a table with sticky notes"
  >
    <p>
      Here you can explain the 'why' behind using a co-design methodology and give an overview of the 6-phase plan. The image could eventually be a diagram of the phases. This section highlights the rigor and empathy of your process.
    </p>
  </FeatureSection>

  <section class="page-outro">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Work in Progress...</h2>
      <p>
        This project is an active and evolving journey. We are currently developing the initial prototype with support from Louis and preparing for the next phases of user testing and evaluation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .team-section {
    padding: 5rem 2rem;
    background-color: var(--color-background);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .team-section h2, .page-hero h1, .page-outro h2 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .team-section .subtitle, .page-hero .subtitle {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: #666;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }
  .page-hero {
    padding: 6rem 2rem;
    text-align: center;
    background-color: var(--color-white);
  }
  .page-outro {
    padding: 5rem 2rem;
    text-align: center;
    background-color: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-white);
  }
  .page-outro h2 {
    color: var(--color-white);
  }
  .page-outro p {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
  }
</style>